[3] Cholera - Uganda (Kasese District)
Date: Mon 23 Mar 2015
Source: African Press Agency (APA) [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/ugandan-hospital-turns-down-drc-cholera-patients.html


Uganda's Bwere General Hospital has blocked cholera victims from the neighboring Democratic Republic of Congo [DRC] from accessing treatment at the health facility in Kasese district, sources confirmed on Monday, 23 Mar 2015. This comes a few days after health officials in Kasese confirmed an outbreak of cholera in the district which they say could have been spread from DRC. At least 6 cholera victims were admitted in the isolation unit at Bwere General Hospital last week [week of 16 Mar 2015].

Most of the victims were residents of Nyabugando ward, which is close to Mpondwe-Lubiriha town council along the Uganda-DRC border. It was reported that cholera had severely affected several villages in Ituri region in DRC forcing several victims to seek treatment from Bwere General Hospital.

Dr Timothy Muke, the head of the Bwera hospital isolation center says management has instead offered to provide medical supplies to health centers in Lubiriha and Kasindi towns in DRC so that patients are treated in their own country. There are more than 40 cholera patients in health centers in Lubiriha and Kasindi towns in DRC.

